      <scopecontent id="aspace_46b38e7a0a4ef879541c7010e502f624">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection consists of correspondence, reports, and receipts pertaining to the business of Alvin Jewett Johnson (1827-1884) of New York City, "publisher of atlases, cyclopedias and other books." Letters from Johnson to his regional supervisor, Lewis W. Fairchild are included, as are letters and weekly reports on sales from local agents and canvassers in Connecticut, Massachusetts, and New York, to Fairchild. The letters and reports concern publication, advertising, and sales of books, problems with competing firms, and the training of salesmen and other employees. Fairchild's personal bills complete the collection.</p>
         <p>These papers were purchased for Yale University in 1965. They were formerly known as the Alvin Johnson Papers.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <altformavail id="aspace_f8034e007fe3fe2fa227b851d0d698f2">
         <head>Existence and Location of Copies</head>
         <p>The entire collection is available on mirofilm (HM 262).</p>  
      </altformavail>
